pageContext.claim: “We delivered 4,000 ventilators to New York, to their warehouse. … It was signed off, they were delivered and they weren't used. And we said, a number of days later, why aren't you using these ventilators? I don't know what happened, but we delivered thousands of them and we've delivered them to a lot of people. There's a whole question about that, I think New York should be fine, based on the numbers that we see. They should have more than enough. I mean, I'm -- I'm hearing stories that they're not used or they're not used right, but what we find anywhere from 2,000 to 4,000 that have been sent and aren't used.”
pageContext.analysis: This makes no sense. New York had not reached the projected apex of covid-19 cases when Trump made these remarks. Gov. Andrew Cuomo said the state would need 30,000 ventilators at the peak. The state would not be returning 2,000 or 4,000 before the number of patients reached a critical stage.
